 /* 8. Array Manipulations

Write a function that manipulates an array of numbers.
· Add {number}: add a number to the end of the array
· Remove {number}: remove all occurrences of a particular number from the array
· RemoveAt {index}: removes number at a given index
· Insert {number} {index}: inserts a number at a given index

Note: All the indices will be valid!

The input comes as an array of strings. The first element will be a string containing the array to manipulate. 
Every other command you receive will also be a string.
The output is the manipulated array printed on the console on a single line, separated by space.

Example
Input Output
['4 19 2 53 6 43', 'Add 3', 'Remove 2', 'RemoveAt 1', 'Insert 8 3'] 4 53 6 8 43 3
['6 12 2 65 6 42', 'Add 8', 'Remove 12', 'RemoveAt 3', 'Insert 6 2'] 6 2 6 65 42 8

Hints
First, we receive the whole input:
· After that we take the first element from the commands and convert it to an array of numbers:
· Then we loop through the commands array, obtain each element from the command, and cast both numbers. This event is called destructuring:  */


function arrayManipulations (arrWithInstructions){

   let newArr = arrWithInstructions[0].split(' ');

   let addElement = arrWithInstructions[1].split(' ');
   newArr.push(addElement[addElement.length-1]);

   let removeElement = arrWithInstructions[2].split(' ');
   let newArrWithRemovedElement = [];
   for (let element of newArr){
      if ( element != removeElement[1]){
      newArrWithRemovedElement.push(element);
      }

   }
   let newArrWithRemovedIndexElement = [];
   let removeIndexElement = arrWithInstructions[3].split(' ');
   for (let y = 0; y < newArrWithRemovedElement.length; y++){
      if (y !== Number(removeIndexElement[1])){
         newArrWithRemovedIndexElement.push(newArrWithRemovedElement[y]);
      }
   }

   let insertElement = arrWithInstructions[4].split(' ');
   let finalArr = [];
   for (let z = 0; z < newArrWithRemovedIndexElement.length; z++){

      if (z == insertElement[2]){
         finalArr.push(insertElement[1]);
      } 
      finalArr.push(newArrWithRemovedIndexElement[z]);

   }
   console.log(finalArr.join(' '));
   }

arrayManipulations(['4 19 2 53 6 43', 'Add 3', 'Remove 2', 'RemoveAt 1', 'Insert 8 3']);
arrayManipulations(['6 12 2 65 6 42', 'Add 8', 'Remove 12', 'RemoveAt 3', 'Insert 6 2']);
